2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed cut-in detection scheme is based on a neural network, which is a common technique used in AI. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a specific Stochastic Model Predictive Controller (SMPC) to enhance the reaction of CACC systems against dangerous cut-in maneuvers. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a neural network for cut-in detection, which is a common technique used in machine learning. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although not explicitly mentioned in the paper, computer vision techniques may be used in the cut-in detection and trajectory prediction scheme.
